29 Chapter 5. High School Diploma Program for Eligible Veterans
30 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "department of veterans' affairs"
31 refers to the Indiana department of veterans' affairs established by
32 IC 10-17-1-2.
33 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "diploma" refers to a high school
34 diploma.
35 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "eligible veteran" refers to an
36 individual who has the following qualifications:
37 (1) Served as a member of the armed forces of the United
38 States at any time during at least one (1) of the following
39 periods:
40 (A) Beginning April 6, 1917, and ending November 11,
41 1918 (World War I).
42 (B) Beginning December 7, 1941, and ending December 31,
EH 1004—LS 6983/DI 110

49
1 1946 (World War II).
2 (C) Beginning June 27, 1950, and ending January 31, 1955
3 (Korean Conflict).
4 (D) Beginning August 5, 1964, and ending May 7, 1975
5 (Vietnam Conflict).
6 (2) Before the military service described in subdivision (1):
7 (A) attended a public or nonpublic high school in Indiana;
8 and
9 (B) was a student in good standing at the high school
10 described in clause (A), to the satisfaction of the
11 department of veterans' affairs.
12 (3) Did not graduate or receive a diploma because of leaving
13 the high school described in subdivision (2) for the military
14 service described in subdivision (1).
15 (4) Was discharged from the armed forces of the United
16 States under conditions other than conditions set forth in
17 IC 10-17-12-7.5(2).
18 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "program" refers to the high
19 school diploma program for eligible veterans established by section
20 6 of this chapter.
21 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "school corporation" includes a
22 successor school corporation serving the area where a high school
23 that no longer exists was once located.
24 Sec. 6. The high school diploma program for eligible veterans is
25 established to provide for the issuance of high school diplomas to
26 certain veterans.
27 Sec. 7. (a) The department and the department of veterans'
28 affairs shall jointly design a form for the application for issuance
29 of a diploma under the program.
30 (b) The application form must require at least the following
31 information about an eligible veteran:
32 (1) Personal identification information.
33 (2) Military service information, including a copy of the
34 eligible veteran's discharge from military service under
35 conditions other than conditions set forth in
36 IC 10-17-12-7.5(2).
37 (3) High school information, including the following:
38 (A) Name and address, including county, of the last high
39 school attended.
40 (B) Whether the high school was a public or nonpublic
41 school.
42 (C) Years attended.
EH 1004—LS 6983/DI 110

50
1 (D) Year of leaving high school to begin military service.
2 (E) Year in which the veteran would have graduated if the
3 veteran had not left high school to begin military service.
4 (4) If the high school attended was a public school, whether
5 the veteran prefers receiving a diploma issued by:
6 (A) the state board; or
7 (B) the governing body of the school corporation governing
8 the high school.
9 Sec. 8. The department of veterans' affairs shall do the following
10 for individuals that the department of veterans' affairs has reason
11 to believe may be eligible to apply for a diploma under the
12 program:
13 (1) Give notice of the program.
14 (2) Describe the application procedure.
15 (3) Furnish an application form.
16 Sec. 9. The following individuals may apply for the issuance of
17 a diploma to an eligible veteran under the program:
18 (1) An eligible veteran, including an eligible veteran who has
19 received a general educational development (GED) diploma
20 issued under IC 20-20-6 (before its repeal) or IC 22-4.1-18, or
21 a similar diploma.
22 (2) An individual who is:
23 (A) the surviving spouse of; or
24 (B) otherwise related to;
25 an eligible veteran who is deceased.
26 Sec. 10. An applicant for a diploma under the program must
27 submit a completed application form to the department of
28 veterans' affairs.
29 Sec. 11. Upon receipt of an application, the department of
30 veterans' affairs shall do the following:
31 (1) Verify the accuracy of the information in the application,
32 in consultation with the department, if necessary.
33 (2) Forward the verified application to the department.
34 Sec. 12. Upon receipt of a verified application, the department
35 shall do the following:
36 (1) If the applicant:
37 (A) expresses a preference in the application to receive a
38 diploma issued by the state board; or
39 (B) attended a nonpublic high school before leaving high
40 school for military service;
41 the department shall present a diploma issued by the state
42 board.
