31 Sec. 13. (a) The commission has the following duties:
32 (1) To adopt rules concerning the following:
33 (A) The use of restraint and seclusion in a school
34 corporation or a state accredited nonpublic school, with an
35 emphasis on eliminating or minimizing the use of restraint
36 and seclusion.
37 (B) The prevention of the use of types of restraint or
38 seclusion that may harm a student, a school employee, a
39 school volunteer, or the educational environment of the
40 school.
41 (C) Requirements for notifying parents.
42 (D) Training regarding the use of restraint and seclusion,
EH 1004—LS 6983/DI 110

68
1 including the frequency of training and what employees
2 must be trained.
3 (E) The distribution of the seclusion and restraint policy to
4 parents and the public.
5 (F) Requirements for the reporting of incidents of restraint
6 and seclusion in the annual school performance report,
7 including incidents of restraint and seclusion involving
8 school resource officers (as defined in IC 20-26-18.2-1).
9 (G) Circumstances that may require more timely incident
10 reporting and the requirements for such reporting.
11 (2) To develop, maintain, and revise a model restraint and
12 seclusion plan for schools that includes the following
13 elements:
14 (A) A statement on how students will be treated with
15 dignity and respect and how appropriate student behavior
16 will be promoted and taught.
17 (B) A statement ensuring that the school will use
18 prevention, positive behavior intervention and support,
19 and conflict de-escalation to eliminate or minimize the
20 need for use of any of the following:
21 (i) Seclusion.
22 (ii) Chemical restraint.
23 (iii) Mechanical restraint.
24 (iv) Physical restraint.
25 (v) Time-out.
26 (C) A statement ensuring that any behavioral intervention
27 used will be consistent with the student's most current
28 behavioral intervention plan, or individualized education
29 program, if applicable.
30 (D) Definitions for restraint and seclusion, as defined in
31 this chapter.
32 (E) A statement ensuring that if a procedure listed in
33 clause (B) is used, the procedure will be used:
34 (i) as a last resort safety procedure, employed only after
35 another, less restrictive procedure has been implemented
36 without success; and
37 (ii) in a situation in which there is an imminent risk of
38 injury to the student, other students, school employees,
39 or visitors to the school.
40 (F) An indication that restraint or seclusion may be used
41 only for a short time period, or until the imminent risk of
42 injury has passed.
EH 1004—LS 6983/DI 110

69
1 (G) A documentation and recording requirement
2 governing instances in which procedures listed in clause
3 (B) are used, including:
4 (i) how every incident will be documented and debriefed;
5 (ii) how responsibilities will be assigned to designated
6 employees for evaluation and oversight; and
7 (iii) designation of a school employee to be the keeper of
8 such documents.
9 (H) A requirement that the student's parent must be
10 notified as soon as possible when an incident involving the
11 student occurs that includes use of procedures listed in
12 clause (B).
13 (I) A requirement that a copy of an incident report must be
14 sent to the student's parent after the student is subject to
15 a procedure listed in clause (B).
16 (J) Required recurrent training for appropriate school
17 employees on the appropriate use of effective alternatives
18 to physical restraint and seclusion, including the use of
19 positive behavioral intervention and support and conflict
20 de-escalation. The training must include the safe use of
21 physical restraint and seclusion in incidents involving
22 imminent danger or serious harm to the student, school
23 employees, or others. Consideration must be given to
24 available school resources and the time commitments of
25 school employees.
26 (3) To accept and review reports from the public and make
27 nonbinding recommendations to the department of any
28 suggested action to be taken.
29 (4) To biannually provide a report to the state advisory
