39 (2) nonpublic school with at least one (1) employee.
40 Sec. 4. (a) The centralized school facilities pilot program is
41 established to provide innovative approaches concerning the use,
42 operation, and management of school facilities to promote:
EH 1004—LS 6983/DI 110

86
1 (1) enhanced learning environments;
2 (2) unique learning opportunities; and
3 (3) improved student academic and health outcomes;
4 in accordance with the plan submitted to the general assembly by
